    <fr:title text="Power Sets">Power Sets</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>The power set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P(A)]]></fr:tex> of a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, is a set whose elements are all of the different possible subsets of A.</html:p>
    <html:p>For a finite set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> with n elements, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P(A)]]></fr:tex> has <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[2^n]]></fr:tex> elements. This is because we can make every subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> by considering a binary choice for each element on whether or note to include it in the set.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
